### 1. Function overview

The `handle_menu_item` function in Bash is used for managing different IPXE (Internet Pre-Boot Execution Environment) menu items. The function itself takes in two arguments: a menu item and a MAC (Media Access Control) address. Depending on the menu item input, the function executes different tasks in an IPXE environment such as initializing the menu, installing hosts, enabling recovery of the DRH (Deployment Runtime Host), showing IPXE information, configuring/deconfiguring hosts, rebooting, local booting, reinstalling, rescuing, running boot installers, and force installing. The function utilizes case statements for handling the different menu items it accepts.

